<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="114" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="114">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="114">The specific epithet is refers to General Ignacio Zaragoza, a hero of the Battle of Puebla (May 1862) against the French Army.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="114" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="114">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="114">This species is distinguished by having petiole and rachis unarmed and twisted. Leaflets are lanceolate, mostly planar, not basally falcate, membranaceous and caniculate, with symmetric apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
